Heat LACTAID(R) Fat Free Milk in a heavy medium-sized saucepan until it starts to boil. Add coconut; remove from heat. Cover and let steep for 20 minutes. Puree LACTAID(R) Fat Free Milk mixture in blender for 3 minutes. In a small bowl, whisk together the sugar, cornstarch and salt. Pour this mixture into the saucepan and whisk in the LACTAID(R) Fat Free Milk mixture and egg. Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens. Pour into mixing bowl, stir in vanilla and let cool completely. Combine pineapple and banana. Evenly divide half of the fruit mixture among 4 glasses. Top with pudding and cover with remaining fruit. Sprinkle with cinnamon and chill for 1 hour.